article.headline: SMU tops Rutgers 70-56
article.story:
PISCATAWAY, N.J. --  Rutgers men's basketball game against Southern Methodist has been postponed due to heavy snow in the area.

The school says Thursday night's game has been rescheduled to Friday. A game time has not been announced.

No. 23 SMU (19-5, 8-3 AAC), ranked in the AP Top 25 for the first time since the 1984-85 season, is seeking its ninth win in 10 games. Rutgers (10-14, 4-7) is looking to earn back-to-back league victories.
